The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Fitch India has signed an MoU with United Bank of India to rate small-scale sector enterprises. The tie-up will help the bank?s SSI customers to get special pricing for ratings. SSIs can claim up to 75 per cent of the rating fees subject to a maximum limit. The scheme will only be applicable to SSIs registered with the National Small Industries Corporation Ltd .

 Tata Motors has launched a range of Tata Safari models. The range is available in three engine options. The Safari DICOR range starts at Rs 6.99 lakh and the Safari petrol range starts at Rs 7.99 lakh.

 Union Bank of India has launched the direct salary scheme for the employees of Calcutta Municipal Corporation. Employees opening an account with the bank will be entitled to features such as zero balance facility and free ATM-cum-debit card. 

 Aptech Ltd has acquired Pune-based Avalon Aviation Academy. Aptech has also inaugurated a training centre at Andheri (west) in Mumbai.

